feat: traditional/Hawaiian scale + live tide data + 6-search beta cap

Three pre-feedback-collection changes:

1. Display heights in Hawaiian/Traditional convention (face / 2, half-foot
   resolution). Engine internals stay in face-height feet; conversion is
   applied only at display boundaries (SpotCard, narration JSON, fallback).
   New util lib/scoring/heightScale.ts. Narration prompt has a new
   "Wave-size convention" section instructing Claude to quote
   surf_height_ft_traditional verbatim, never face-multiply, and use
   shoulder-/head-/overhead vocabulary.

2. Wire real tide data via Open-Meteo's existing sea_level_height_msl
   field — zero new auth, zero quota risk, no signup. Phase (low/mid_low/
   mid/mid_high/high) and direction (rising/falling) are derived from a
   ±3-hour window in the hourly time series. tideFactor now implements
   spec §4: low-sensitivity spots stay at 1.0; medium and high apply the
   in-window / adjacent / far multipliers + ±0.03 trajectory bonus.
   Preference strings ("Mid to high", "Most tides", "Variable", etc.) are
   parsed by a new lib/scoring/tidePreference.ts module. When the field
   is missing or out-of-coverage, tideFactor falls back to 1.0 + a
   "tide unavailable" caveat — request never fails on tide alone.
   LiveConditions.tideState replaced with structured TideState type.

3. Soft 6-search-per-browser limit via localStorage (key:
   swell.searchCount). Counter increments only on stream completion
   (frame.type === 'done'), so failed/aborted searches don't burn budget.
   On the 6th attempt a "Search 6 of 6" line appears below the submit
   button. The 7th submit replaces the form with a friendly limit-reached
   notice + Google Form link. No backend rate limiting; this is a
   testing-phase soft cap, not abuse prevention.

Verified live (today's Melbourne morning):
- Fairhaven face=4.9ft -> trad=2.5ft, tide phase=low/falling, factor=1.0
- Flinders face=5.5ft -> trad=2.5ft, factor=1.02 (medium sensitivity)
- Bells Beach face=4.1ft -> trad=2ft, factor=1.02 (medium, unconstrained)

276/276 tests pass; tsc clean; lint 0 errors.

